"script": "The International Space Station isn't floating up there. It's actually falling toward Earth right now, and it never stops. You see, gravity still pulls on it, just like it pulls on you. But the station is also racing sideways at 17,500 miles per hour. So as it falls, the Earth curves away beneath it just as fast, and it keeps missing the ground. That endless plunge is what we call orbit. And the astronauts inside feel weightless not because gravity is gone, but because they're falling with the station, forever.",
